WEBVTT

00:05.239 --> 00:10.275
Patty Wilson, please tell us
what is your favorite hobby?

00:11.711 --> 00:13.445
I like going to school

00:13.447 --> 00:15.514
- and playing the violin.
- No. No.

00:15.516 --> 00:17.756
Patty Wilson, please tell us
what is your favorite hobby?

00:19.252 --> 00:21.220
I like helping the homeless.

00:21.222 --> 00:23.455
Right. Great, great, great.

00:23.457 --> 00:25.424
Ok, if anybody ever
asks you anything,

00:25.426 --> 00:28.127
you always answer
with charity, Ok?

00:28.129 --> 00:32.363
Homeless, pets,
old people, doesn't matter.

00:33.900 --> 00:35.734
This is your pageant, honey.

00:35.736 --> 00:38.370
You're going to take this one
I know it.

00:40.000 --> 00:46.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:21.916 --> 01:23.282
Thank you.

02:52.305 --> 02:54.740
We are now
onto the interview portion

02:54.742 --> 02:56.041
of our competition.

02:56.043 --> 03:00.579
Our first contestant
is Taylor Rollins.

03:02.716 --> 03:04.883
Taylor is 11 years old,

03:04.885 --> 03:07.953
and says her favorite
animal is a kitten.

03:07.955 --> 03:11.957
And her favorite color is pink.

03:14.295 --> 03:18.330
Taylor, dear, what has been
the most proud moment

03:18.332 --> 03:19.798
of your life?

03:19.800 --> 03:22.668
Well, I'd have to say
that I was most proud

03:22.670 --> 03:25.003
of myself when I volunteered
in a children's hospital

03:25.005 --> 03:26.505
over the summer.

03:26.507 --> 03:28.573
I felt very lucky
to be able to help kids

03:28.575 --> 03:30.709
who weren't as
fortunate as I am.

03:30.711 --> 03:34.046
Well, that is definitely
something to be proud of!

03:34.048 --> 03:35.447
Thank you, Taylor.

03:37.484 --> 03:39.318
That girl only stopped
peeing the bed

03:39.320 --> 03:40.552
- like three months ago.
- Leanne!

03:40.554 --> 03:41.787
And now...

03:41.789 --> 03:44.956
Our next contestant,
Ms. Patty Wilson

03:46.527 --> 03:47.527
my baby!

03:51.731 --> 03:52.898
My baby!

03:52.900 --> 03:54.466
Patty's from Austin.

03:54.468 --> 03:56.768
Patty's favorite color is...

03:56.770 --> 03:57.770
Gray?

04:00.907 --> 04:04.509
Ok, Patty, your question is

04:04.511 --> 04:08.547
what's the biggest challenge
facing young girls today?

04:10.049 --> 04:11.049
Hmm.

04:15.355 --> 04:18.390
Society's pressure
on girls to look perfect.

04:20.059 --> 04:24.663
This emphasis on appearance
is linked to three most common

04:24.665 --> 04:27.065
mental health problems
that we have today,

04:28.468 --> 04:31.403
low self-esteem,
eating disorders,

04:31.405 --> 04:32.604
and depression.

04:37.543 --> 04:39.745
Ok, thank you, Patty.

04:45.685 --> 04:49.588
Well, that's definitely
something to be proud of.

04:49.590 --> 04:52.090
All right, then,
now, our next contestant,

05:03.569 --> 05:04.870
what the heck was that?

05:04.872 --> 05:07.606
And why would you
say that at pageant?

05:07.608 --> 05:09.541
Well, it is true,

05:09.543 --> 05:10.709
and I thought
the right thing to do

05:10.711 --> 05:11.843
was to tell the truth.

05:11.845 --> 05:14.513
Honey, the truth is relative.

05:14.515 --> 05:16.415
The plain and simple truth
is really plain,

05:16.417 --> 05:18.517
and it's never simple,
so remember that, Ok?

05:18.519 --> 05:20.752
Well, I thought
you did a great job.

05:20.754 --> 05:21.920
I'm very proud of
you, sweetheart.

05:21.922 --> 05:22.922
Thanks, dad.

05:24.123 --> 05:26.091
Me, too.
You were the best one out there.

05:26.093 --> 05:28.026
You had it won, but you
took your eye off the prize.

05:28.028 --> 05:30.061
You gotta keep your eye
on the prize, baby.

05:30.063 --> 05:32.831
The prize is in
the eye of the beholder.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.065
That is the spirit!

05:43.042 --> 05:44.176
There we go.

05:52.051 --> 05:54.052
If only we had more money,

05:54.054 --> 05:55.887
you'd be training with somebody
from dare to dance

05:55.889 --> 05:57.522
like Taylor's doing.

05:57.524 --> 06:00.892
God, if you'd only got
that promotion, don.

06:02.628 --> 06:04.463
Oh, sorry.

06:04.465 --> 06:06.698
Stan Buford got it.
He's dating the boss's daughter,

06:06.700 --> 06:08.420
so unless you want me
to start doing that...

06:11.771 --> 06:14.039
Don't worry, daddy.
You'll get the next one.

06:14.041 --> 06:15.974
Don't hold your breath, honey.

06:15.976 --> 06:17.576
You know what they say,

06:17.578 --> 06:19.044
the world would be
a much better place

06:19.046 --> 06:21.046
if it were run by women,
and I think you could do it.

06:21.048 --> 06:22.814
You're so talented.

06:22.816 --> 06:24.182
You remind me of me
when I was little.

06:24.184 --> 06:25.717
Only you're better.

06:25.719 --> 06:27.986
The only way to make it
in this business, honey,

06:27.988 --> 06:29.221
is to be a triple threat.

06:29.223 --> 06:30.622
Look at Miley.

06:30.624 --> 06:32.924
Great role model, mom.

06:32.926 --> 06:34.793
Yeah, she's a triple threat.

06:34.795 --> 06:37.562
She can sing, dance,
and take of all her clothes.

06:37.564 --> 06:39.498
Well, she's got a great body.

06:39.500 --> 06:40.866
She works very hard for that.

06:40.868 --> 06:42.801
Why not show it off?
I wish I had done it.

06:42.803 --> 06:44.503
I wish I had done
it when I was young.

06:44.505 --> 06:47.506
I would have showed
it all off, now, in hindsight.

06:47.508 --> 06:50.108
Doesn't Miley just go around
licking everything or...

06:50.110 --> 06:52.577
Well, sometimes you
have to sacrifice, don.

06:52.579 --> 06:53.899
Sometimes you have
to lick things.

06:59.852 --> 07:01.286
<i>Carrie Clark
took the stand today</i>

07:01.288 --> 07:04.089
<i>in the federal trial
of Jakob Todd Mitchum.</i>

07:04.091 --> 07:05.757
<i>He's the man who abducted her</i>

07:05.759 --> 07:08.293
<i>and held her captive
nearly 10 years ago.</i>

07:08.295 --> 07:10.228
<i>After only five hours
of deliberation,</i>

07:10.230 --> 07:13.231
<i>the jury found Mitchum
guilty of kidnapping</i>

07:13.233 --> 07:15.300
and sex crimes against a minor.

07:15.302 --> 07:16.902
<i>Carrie arrived at the courthouse</i>

07:16.904 --> 07:18.670
<i>with her parents,
Lou and Carolyn Clark,</i>

07:18.672 --> 07:20.906
<i>who spoke to reporters
after the verdict.</i>

07:20.908 --> 07:23.141
<i>We're just so happy that
this whole nightmare is over</i>

07:23.143 --> 07:25.310
<i>and that Carrie is back
home with us again.</i>

07:25.312 --> 07:27.612
<i>It's been such a
life-changing ordeal,</i>

07:27.614 --> 07:29.014
<i>and I think writing this book,</i>

07:29.016 --> 07:31.816
carry me home:
The Carrie Clark story,

07:31.818 --> 07:34.052
<i>will be very cathartic for me.</i>

07:34.054 --> 07:37.789
All right, geez,
what a media whore.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.791
I think she was just feeling
a sense of relief

07:39.793 --> 07:41.226
from finally having
some good news, babe.

07:41.228 --> 07:42.928
Whatever.

07:42.930 --> 07:46.131
A look into the ongoing struggle
to keep Austin weird.

07:49.036 --> 07:51.236
<i>My-my ear piece's not working.
I can't hear anything.</i>

08:12.224 --> 08:14.159
All right, Patty,
it's time for bed.

08:14.161 --> 08:15.860
Mom, I've almost got
this piece down.

08:15.862 --> 08:17.295
- Come on.
- You see there's this part

08:17.297 --> 08:19.230
- that keeps tripping me up.
- I know, I know.

08:19.232 --> 08:20.765
But if I only practice
that section,

08:20.767 --> 08:22.200
- the piece will be perfect.
- Time for bed.

08:22.202 --> 08:23.335
I could kill your father
for giving you this thing.

08:23.337 --> 08:24.970
Come on, time for bed. Jump in.

08:26.706 --> 08:28.139
You know if you're going
to be up late practicing,

08:28.141 --> 08:29.808
you should be practicing
your new choreography

08:29.810 --> 08:30.810
for your jazz solo.

08:32.144 --> 08:34.712
Mrs. Patterson says
I'm really good.

08:34.715 --> 08:36.648
Says I can even do this
for the talent competition.

08:36.650 --> 08:38.616
Oh, honey,
that's not gonna happen.

08:38.619 --> 08:41.186
I love the way you play.
I'm so proud of you,

08:41.188 --> 08:42.886
but trust me,

08:42.889 --> 08:43.989
nobody's ever won
<i>America's got talent</i>

08:43.991 --> 08:45.390
playing a fiddle.

08:45.392 --> 08:47.993
It's not a fiddle.
It's a violin.

08:47.995 --> 08:50.028
Ok, a violin.

08:50.030 --> 08:52.030
I mean, maybe you get
to be a contestant,

08:52.032 --> 08:53.032
but you don't get to win.

08:54.100 --> 08:55.634
Dancing is fun.

08:55.636 --> 08:57.902
- Mom.
- It's sassy.

08:57.904 --> 08:58.904
People love it.

09:00.106 --> 09:01.106
You still mad?

09:02.274 --> 09:04.309
No. I'm over it now.

09:06.846 --> 09:08.179
You looked amazing,

09:08.181 --> 09:10.382
and before you gave
everyone a coronary,

09:10.384 --> 09:12.050
you were doing real good.

09:13.419 --> 09:15.787
Lay down. Get to bed, come on.

09:17.724 --> 09:21.826
Mom, are you sure I can't go
to Rhonda's birthday party?

09:21.828 --> 09:24.729
Rollerskating?
Oh, absolutely not, baby.

09:24.731 --> 09:26.898
What if you got a nasty
bruise or you get hurt?

09:26.900 --> 09:29.300
Mom, please.
It's so embarrassing.

09:29.302 --> 09:31.903
I'm always left out of the fun.

09:31.905 --> 09:33.838
Baby, I don't want you
to throw away your future

09:33.840 --> 09:34.839
on a dumb, little party.

09:34.841 --> 09:36.741
Look, I know it stinks,

09:36.743 --> 09:38.877
but I wish my momma
would have pushed me harder.

09:40.212 --> 09:42.313
Oh, you have jazz
and ballet tomorrow.

09:42.315 --> 09:44.115
I'm going to drop you
off before I go to work.

09:46.886 --> 09:48.119
I love you.

09:50.122 --> 09:51.322
- See you in the morning.
- Goodnight, mom.

09:51.324 --> 09:52.324
Goodnight, baby.

09:59.832 --> 10:01.700
This one declined, too.

10:01.702 --> 10:02.734
What?

10:04.403 --> 10:06.471
You know what,
I'll just write a check.

10:06.473 --> 10:09.207
Actually we don't accept checks
from you anymore.

10:09.209 --> 10:11.710
It's $25 after they bounce.

10:13.713 --> 10:15.280
Come on, Kandy,
cut me some slack.

10:15.282 --> 10:16.948
I really wish I could, Leanne,

10:16.950 --> 10:20.251
but if we don't get
Patty's tuition in full,

10:20.253 --> 10:22.020
she can't start her
new classes next week.

10:23.055 --> 10:24.422
And we all love Patty,

10:24.424 --> 10:27.092
so I really hope you can
figure something out.

10:28.928 --> 10:31.930
All right, you know what,
I wanted the airline points,

10:31.932 --> 10:33.431
but whatever,

10:34.734 --> 10:36.501
just put it on this.

10:36.503 --> 10:38.269
That's a coffee card.

10:38.271 --> 10:39.504
Just take it.

10:43.342 --> 10:45.910
Great.
You know I'm late for work,

10:45.912 --> 10:49.314
so I will grab that
when I bring Patty for class.

10:49.316 --> 10:51.282
Thank you! Bye, Donna.

11:05.765 --> 11:08.233
Shit, shit, shit,
shit, shit! Fuck!

11:15.508 --> 11:16.541
Where have you been?

11:16.543 --> 11:18.143
I got here as soon as I could

11:18.145 --> 11:19.511
I had to deal with
Patty's choreography,

11:19.513 --> 11:21.312
- Leanne.
- Hi.

11:21.314 --> 11:22.814
I swear if you're even
10 seconds late again,

11:22.816 --> 11:24.482
you're out.

11:24.484 --> 11:27.085
Jose, my car wouldn't start,
and then it got all smokey,

11:27.087 --> 11:29.454
- and I couldn't see anything.
- Not interested.

11:29.456 --> 11:31.055
Nice try.

11:31.057 --> 11:33.224
Leanne,
your next client is here.

11:33.226 --> 11:35.026
She's been waiting.
Let me get her.

11:41.500 --> 11:43.067
Please tell me
this isn't happening.

11:43.069 --> 11:45.336
This is our fabulous
makeup artist, Leanne.

11:45.338 --> 11:48.273
Leanne milling!
Oh, my god!

11:48.275 --> 11:50.341
Shut up! Crystal Clemens?

11:50.343 --> 11:52.143
I know!

11:52.145 --> 11:54.512
I don't think I've seen you
since our Avon days.

11:54.514 --> 11:55.980
Time just flies
right past, right?

11:55.982 --> 11:57.148
It sure does,

11:57.150 --> 11:58.316
but you look just
as good as ever.

11:58.318 --> 12:00.051
Oh, shut up, really?

12:00.053 --> 12:02.053
Are you kidding me,
you're still a beauty queen.

12:02.055 --> 12:03.988
Oh, my beauty queen
days are over.

12:03.990 --> 12:06.191
I'm a momma now.
Doing the momma thing.

12:06.193 --> 12:07.458
Get out!

12:07.460 --> 12:08.993
How many kids do you have?

12:08.995 --> 12:10.595
Just one.
She's my little Princess.

12:10.597 --> 12:13.264
Her name is Patricia,
but I call her Patty.

12:13.266 --> 12:14.899
She's picking up right
where I left off.

12:14.901 --> 12:16.301
Oh, that is just precious.

12:16.303 --> 12:18.036
I bet she's gonna be
a winner just like you.

12:19.471 --> 12:22.440
Well, let's get you
in the makeup chair.

12:23.542 --> 12:24.976
No kids for me yet.

12:24.978 --> 12:26.444
Not with our hectic schedule.

12:26.446 --> 12:27.912
My husband's an old man.

12:28.981 --> 12:30.348
How old is he?

12:30.350 --> 12:32.584
No, "oil" man.

12:32.586 --> 12:34.519
- Oh, oil. Wow.
- Yeah.

12:34.521 --> 12:37.322
I mean, but he's old, too,
so, whatever.

12:37.324 --> 12:39.457
Every other day,
we got some kinda party

12:39.459 --> 12:41.192
or event we gotta go to.

12:41.194 --> 12:42.894
Oh, we're also building
our dream house

12:42.896 --> 12:44.996
up in Aspen right now, so, yeah.

12:44.998 --> 12:47.031
Anyway, I'm sure once
all that settles down,

12:47.033 --> 12:50.001
we'll probably, you know,
pop out a couple.

12:50.003 --> 12:53.104
Well, what are we
going to do today?

12:53.106 --> 12:54.939
Oh, well, we have this huge
black-tie charity event

12:54.941 --> 12:57.208
to go to for children
in Africa or somewhere,

12:57.210 --> 12:59.477
I don't know, anyway,
the governor's gonna be there.

12:59.479 --> 13:02.180
I just want to look really good
in case the cameras are rolling.

13:02.182 --> 13:04.082
Anyway, I just keep going on
and on about me,

13:04.084 --> 13:05.149
tell me about you.
What is going on?

13:05.151 --> 13:06.517
How have you been?

13:06.519 --> 13:08.620
Did you marry
that hot boyfriend of yours?

13:08.622 --> 13:11.089
I swear I always thought
I was going to see you

13:11.091 --> 13:12.557
on <i>days of our lives</i>
<i>or something.</i>

13:12.559 --> 13:14.659
- Stop it.
- I did.

13:14.661 --> 13:16.194
What are you
talking about Billy?

13:16.196 --> 13:18.663
Oh, please, honey,
I outgrew all of that

13:18.665 --> 13:20.365
when don came along.

13:20.367 --> 13:23.034
He just walked in
and swept me off my feet.

13:23.036 --> 13:24.969
I mean his business
was just blowing up,

13:24.971 --> 13:27.171
so we moved to Austin.

13:27.173 --> 13:30.942
Yeah, you know, he's a super
successful computer guy.

13:30.944 --> 13:32.377
Well, then good for you

13:32.379 --> 13:33.978
for doing these
little makeup jobs

13:33.980 --> 13:34.980
and helping chip in.

13:36.548 --> 13:39.484
Well, you know what,
I don't even have to do this,

13:39.486 --> 13:41.920
- hm-mm.
- But I love it, it's a passion.

13:41.922 --> 13:44.555
So, I needed a little
creative outlet.

13:44.557 --> 13:47.258
I come in here whenever I want.

13:47.260 --> 13:48.526
You just work whenever?

13:48.528 --> 13:50.662
Yeah, my own schedule,
my own life.

13:50.664 --> 13:52.297
For me, I mean,
when you're a mom,

13:52.299 --> 13:53.531
I mean, I know you
don't know yet,

13:53.533 --> 13:55.300
but sometimes when
you are a mom,

13:55.302 --> 13:57.001
you just need a little me time.

13:57.003 --> 13:59.504
Understood.
Whatever you can get.

13:59.506 --> 14:02.006
Whatever works for you.

14:02.008 --> 14:03.408
You know what?
I'm actually just talking

14:03.410 --> 14:05.476
way too much,
and you should be relaxing,

14:05.478 --> 14:07.312
so why don't you lay back,

14:07.314 --> 14:08.713
and as soon as you finish
reading that magazine,

14:08.715 --> 14:10.014
you'll be gorgeous.

14:10.016 --> 14:11.049
Ok.

14:11.051 --> 14:12.483
Oh, this poor girl.

14:12.485 --> 14:15.520
I swear I have seen her
on so many interviews.

14:15.522 --> 14:17.722
And her parents have
done the rounds, too.

14:17.724 --> 14:19.524
They're always so positive.

14:19.526 --> 14:21.726
I don't think I could do it.

14:21.728 --> 14:23.628
I know I couldn't do it.

14:26.266 --> 14:28.333
Oh, my god!

14:28.335 --> 14:30.335
Leanne, are you Ok?

14:30.337 --> 14:31.369
Oh, I can't move.

14:31.371 --> 14:33.171
Call the ambulance.

14:33.173 --> 14:35.506
- Oh, it hurts so bad.
- Here, honey, look I'm sorry,

14:35.508 --> 14:38.209
but I really gotta get
somebody to finish my face.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.377
Sorry.

14:39.379 --> 14:41.546
What, what?

14:41.548 --> 14:44.015
Relax, calm down.
The medics are on their way.

14:46.151 --> 14:47.285
Damn it.

14:49.355 --> 14:50.488
Oh, shit.

14:53.692 --> 14:55.326
You know it's bad enough
I fall on my ass

14:55.328 --> 14:56.494
in front of everybody
in the salon,

14:56.496 --> 14:58.062
but in front of crystal Clemens.

14:58.064 --> 14:59.464
What do you care
what that dummy thinks?

14:59.466 --> 15:02.734
Because, don, I worked
with her at Avon.

15:02.736 --> 15:04.569
She was like this
little, annoying dog

15:04.571 --> 15:05.770
that was always
nipping at my heels

15:05.772 --> 15:07.238
wanting everything that I had.

15:08.574 --> 15:10.541
Boy, how the tides have turned.

15:10.543 --> 15:12.510
Coming in there talking
about her rich husband,

15:12.512 --> 15:14.512
and her giant mansions,
and, "oh, I gotta look good

15:14.514 --> 15:17.682
in case my cameras are rolling."

15:17.684 --> 15:19.384
I bet she didn't even have
a charity thing to go to,

15:19.386 --> 15:20.718
I bet she just wanted
to come in there

15:20.720 --> 15:23.521
and rub her fabulous
life in my face.

15:23.523 --> 15:25.443
I didn't know you thought
your life was so lousy.

15:27.326 --> 15:29.627
Oh, don, come on,
you know what I meant.

15:29.629 --> 15:31.362
I just always thought
that I was going to be,

15:31.364 --> 15:33.398
you know, something more.

15:35.768 --> 15:39.437
Well, why don't you just,
you know,

15:39.439 --> 15:41.305
put the focus
a little less on Patty

15:41.307 --> 15:42.473
and a little bit more on you,

15:42.475 --> 15:44.275
do something that
makes you happy.

15:44.277 --> 15:45.743
Why don't you take
a dance class again?

15:45.745 --> 15:47.779
You love that salsa dancing
or whatever, right?

15:47.781 --> 15:49.480
With what money, don?

15:49.482 --> 15:51.215
I don't even know
how we're going to pay

15:51.217 --> 15:52.857
for Patty's classes
now that I can't work.

15:54.053 --> 15:56.187
God, she's gonna
be so disappointed.

15:56.189 --> 15:57.355
Well, you know,
maybe we can scale back

15:57.357 --> 15:58.689
on Patty's activities.

15:58.691 --> 16:02.126
I think it might be
good for her, possibly.

16:04.630 --> 16:07.532
You know what,
Donny, I'm real tired.

16:07.534 --> 16:09.534
I don't feel so good.
I'm just going to go to sleep.

16:09.536 --> 16:10.536
- Ok.
- Hey.

16:11.603 --> 16:13.104
Rub my feet 'til I fall asleep.

