01:19:51.354 --> 01:19:53.254
You're not looking
too hot these days.

01:19:53.256 --> 01:19:54.421
A little old if you ask me.

01:19:56.324 --> 01:19:58.259
- Excuse me?
- Yeah, that's right.

01:19:58.261 --> 01:19:59.994
I think it'd be about time
to trade you in

01:19:59.996 --> 01:20:01.896
on a newer model anyway.

01:20:04.333 --> 01:20:06.166
Now let's both be honest.

01:20:06.168 --> 01:20:08.969
We both know I had your dumb ass
wrapped around my little finger,

01:20:08.971 --> 01:20:10.905
but I guess some things
never change.

01:20:13.608 --> 01:20:15.643
Don't think you're gonna
get over on me,

01:20:15.645 --> 01:20:18.078
you are crazy.

01:20:18.080 --> 01:20:19.914
I'll tell your brat
you said goodbye.

01:20:33.161 --> 01:20:34.328
Holy crap.

01:21:37.392 --> 01:21:39.293
Jesus, Billy.

01:21:40.428 --> 01:21:42.663
Why'd you make me do that?

01:22:27.108 --> 01:22:28.142
Baby.

01:22:29.411 --> 01:22:31.545
I'm gonna explain
everything, Ok.

01:22:31.547 --> 01:22:33.814
Listen, baby, I just...

01:22:33.816 --> 01:22:35.049
Oh, my god!

01:22:39.421 --> 01:22:41.355
What the hell happened to Billy?

01:22:41.357 --> 01:22:43.757
He left me no choice, JT.
It was self-defense.

01:22:43.759 --> 01:22:44.825
I swear to god.

01:22:44.827 --> 01:22:46.460
He was... he... he...

01:22:53.201 --> 01:22:56.570
He loved you.
And you just was lying to him.

01:22:56.572 --> 01:22:58.539
You're husband's
not abusive at all, is he?

01:23:01.176 --> 01:23:03.577
Mom, why would you do this?

01:23:13.621 --> 01:23:18.692
Baby, this is going to
set us up for life.

01:23:18.694 --> 01:23:22.296
I hated that you were here
and that you were scared,

01:23:22.298 --> 01:23:25.632
but I knew when the public took
one look at your face,

01:23:25.634 --> 01:23:28.735
they would see
that you're a star,

01:23:28.737 --> 01:23:30.337
like you're destined to be.

01:23:33.741 --> 01:23:38.445
Mom, you never hear me.

01:23:39.781 --> 01:23:42.116
This is so horrible,
even for you.

01:23:44.552 --> 01:23:46.420
Wait, dad doesn't know
you did this, does he?

01:23:47.722 --> 01:23:49.323
No, baby,

01:23:49.325 --> 01:23:51.291
daddy's not strong enough
to go through

01:23:51.293 --> 01:23:53.293
with a plan like this,

01:23:53.295 --> 01:23:55.896
and I know you don't see it now,
but I did this for our family.

01:23:57.532 --> 01:24:01.368
This... this is going to be
a distant memory,

01:24:01.370 --> 01:24:02.703
and the rest of your life

01:24:02.705 --> 01:24:05.606
is going to be like
a dream come true, baby.

01:24:05.608 --> 01:24:09.476
Stop saying that.
It's just not true.

01:24:10.678 --> 01:24:12.279
You did this all for yourself.

01:24:34.802 --> 01:24:36.637
Oh, honey.

01:24:38.306 --> 01:24:40.207
You just have no idea

01:24:40.209 --> 01:24:43.310
what it's like to look back
on your life and see regrets.

01:24:44.445 --> 01:24:46.180
Nothing is worse

01:24:46.182 --> 01:24:47.748
than wondering what your life
could've been like

01:24:47.750 --> 01:24:49.583
if you would have
done things differently

01:24:49.585 --> 01:24:52.219
or taken bigger risks,
and I don't want that for you.

01:24:54.222 --> 01:24:56.823
So I saw an opportunity
this time, and I took it.

01:24:58.259 --> 01:24:59.693
But things just
got out of control.

01:24:59.695 --> 01:25:01.728
Sometimes, you just go too far,

01:25:01.730 --> 01:25:03.497
and you just can't
find your way back.

01:25:05.233 --> 01:25:07.801
But now we are just going to
keep pressing forward.

01:25:14.343 --> 01:25:17.377
Were you cheating on dad
with that creep?

01:25:18.479 --> 01:25:20.714
God, no, honey. Of course not.

01:25:24.285 --> 01:25:25.719
And don't you worry
about those two.

01:25:25.721 --> 01:25:27.254
I'm gonna take care of them.

01:25:28.489 --> 01:25:29.890
Mom, you better leave JT alone.

01:25:32.660 --> 01:25:34.962
He's my friend,
and he's taking good care of me.

01:25:34.964 --> 01:25:36.630
Honey, I'm glad you liked him,

01:25:36.632 --> 01:25:38.765
but that man could cause
a lot of trouble for us, Ok?

01:25:38.767 --> 01:25:39.766
You don't really know him.

01:25:39.768 --> 01:25:42.269
No, you don't know him!

01:25:42.271 --> 01:25:45.839
I'm telling you this, mother,
if anything happens to JT,

01:25:45.841 --> 01:25:47.608
I will tell the whole world
what you've done.

01:25:47.610 --> 01:25:49.309
Excuse me?

01:25:49.311 --> 01:25:50.644
Now you listen to me,
little lady.

01:25:50.646 --> 01:25:52.746
No, you listen.

01:25:52.748 --> 01:25:55.849
I'm not going to let
my friend get hurt

01:25:55.851 --> 01:25:57.884
because of your crazy scheming.

01:25:58.920 --> 01:26:00.954
I'm so serious.

01:26:06.561 --> 01:26:08.121
You wouldn't do that
to your own mother.

01:26:09.664 --> 01:26:11.932
Yeah, what, you're gonna
get rid of me, too, now?

01:26:14.602 --> 01:26:16.503
Ok. Ok.

01:26:43.831 --> 01:26:44.898
Ok.

01:26:57.679 --> 01:26:59.880
JT, can we talk to you
for a minute, please?

01:27:02.583 --> 01:27:03.583
Come on out here.

01:27:04.786 --> 01:27:06.586
Everything Ok out here?

01:27:06.588 --> 01:27:07.688
Of course.

01:27:09.824 --> 01:27:11.925
I wanted to say thank you

01:27:11.927 --> 01:27:13.927
for taking such good care
of my little girl,

01:27:13.929 --> 01:27:15.862
for keeping her safe,

01:27:15.864 --> 01:27:18.598
and I also wanted to say
that I'm very sorry

01:27:18.600 --> 01:27:19.800
for what happened to Billy.

01:27:21.803 --> 01:27:24.604
Please know that what I did,
I did for all of our sakes.

01:27:29.577 --> 01:27:30.844
And I'm also very sorry

01:27:30.846 --> 01:27:32.446
for what I'm about to do
right now.

01:27:33.481 --> 01:27:34.481
Huh?

01:27:43.925 --> 01:27:46.460
Thank you all for being here.

01:27:46.462 --> 01:27:50.397
I stand here upon this,
uh, stage, if you will,

01:27:50.399 --> 01:27:52.733
I'm reminded of a quote
by will Shakespeare,

01:27:52.735 --> 01:27:55.869
"cowards die many times
before their deaths.

01:27:55.871 --> 01:27:59.573
The Valiant never taste
of death, but once."

01:28:04.580 --> 01:28:08.415
The alleged kidnapper,
this coward of a man,

01:28:08.417 --> 01:28:09.850
is deceased.

01:28:09.852 --> 01:28:13.653
He was identified
as 40-year-old William Fontaine.

01:28:13.655 --> 01:28:16.390
The crime seems to be that
of a personal vendetta.

01:28:18.626 --> 01:28:21.428
This investigation is ongoing,

01:28:21.430 --> 01:28:22.429
so I can't tell you
any more than the facts

01:28:22.431 --> 01:28:23.497
at this moment.

01:28:23.499 --> 01:28:24.865
I can tell you, however,

01:28:24.867 --> 01:28:28.168
there does appear to be
a hero in this story,

01:28:29.937 --> 01:28:33.774
the Valiant,
Mr. Jebediah Thompson.

01:28:36.512 --> 01:28:39.179
Mr. Thompson was acquainted
with Mr. Fontaine,

01:28:39.181 --> 01:28:42.115
who knew that Mr. Thompson
owned a secluded cabin

01:28:42.117 --> 01:28:44.484
in a remote wooded area.

01:28:44.486 --> 01:28:45.919
This is where
he took Patty Wilson,

01:28:46.954 --> 01:28:48.455
and where they remained

01:28:48.457 --> 01:28:51.091
until Mr. Thompson
made an unexpected visit

01:28:51.093 --> 01:28:53.727
to that cabin
and discovered them.

01:28:53.729 --> 01:28:56.563
At this point, he realized
that she was a missing child,

01:28:56.565 --> 01:28:58.064
made an attempt to rescue her,

01:28:58.066 --> 01:29:01.601
a fight ensued,
leading to his death.

01:29:02.670 --> 01:29:05.639
JT is a rare breed.

01:29:05.641 --> 01:29:08.742
We'd like to thank
him for his courage

01:29:08.744 --> 01:29:10.010
and for rescuing Patty Wilson.

01:29:22.190 --> 01:29:26.460
Uh, at this moment, Mrs. Wilson
would like to make a statement.

01:29:31.867 --> 01:29:33.533
Hello.

01:29:35.838 --> 01:29:38.238
<i>Well, I just wanna say</i>

01:29:38.240 --> 01:29:39.873
we are over the moon

01:29:39.875 --> 01:29:41.508
to have our precious
daughter back,

01:29:41.510 --> 01:29:43.176
and I want to sincerely
thank the FBI,

01:29:46.080 --> 01:29:49.950
sheriff Williams,
and the entire department,

01:29:49.952 --> 01:29:52.486
as well as this community,

01:29:52.488 --> 01:29:54.654
for your compassion
and your generosity

01:29:54.656 --> 01:29:58.892
and your assistance
during this horrific ordeal.

01:30:00.061 --> 01:30:01.695
Don and I are so proud

01:30:01.697 --> 01:30:04.231
of what a strong and
resilient girl Patty is,

01:30:04.233 --> 01:30:06.166
and we're so happy

01:30:06.168 --> 01:30:08.935
that she's going to be able to
show the world her talents.

01:30:10.972 --> 01:30:12.873
<i>But I really want
to take a moment</i>

01:30:12.875 --> 01:30:15.575
to give thanks to JT.

01:30:17.144 --> 01:30:19.880
Because of this brave man,
we have our baby back.

01:30:21.015 --> 01:30:23.617
He'll always be our hero,

01:30:23.619 --> 01:30:25.218
and we can never
thank him enough.

01:30:27.756 --> 01:30:29.623
One last thing.
One last thing, thank you.

01:30:29.625 --> 01:30:30.657
One last thing.

01:30:30.659 --> 01:30:32.225
<i>I want to thank the lord.</i>

01:30:32.227 --> 01:30:35.228
<i>Thank you, for bringing back
our little girl...</i>

01:30:37.198 --> 01:30:38.665
<i>Safe and sound,</i>

01:30:40.001 --> 01:30:41.268
<i>and I want to thank all of you.</i>

01:30:42.303 --> 01:30:43.303
<i>God bless you.</i>

01:31:32.787 --> 01:31:35.188
Well, if it isn't
Leanne milling.

01:31:35.190 --> 01:31:36.890
Oh, I don't have time
for an interview, now, honey.

01:31:36.892 --> 01:31:38.258
I'm meeting someone.

01:31:38.260 --> 01:31:42.195
Yeah, I know, you're late.
Have a seat.

01:31:44.999 --> 01:31:46.166
Join me.

01:31:55.676 --> 01:31:58.612
How dare you send me
that ridiculous text.

01:31:58.614 --> 01:31:59.614
Oh.

01:32:01.082 --> 01:32:04.884
Hello, uh, can I get an iced tea
unsweetened, two lemons?

01:32:04.886 --> 01:32:07.754
I'll have the same, but sweet,
very sweet.

01:32:08.789 --> 01:32:10.857
You're Leanne Wilson.

01:32:10.859 --> 01:32:12.626
My momma says
you're an inspiration.

01:32:13.661 --> 01:32:15.028
That is so kind.

01:32:15.030 --> 01:32:17.831
Please tell your momma,
thank you for her love

01:32:17.833 --> 01:32:18.999
and support and prayers.

01:32:20.067 --> 01:32:21.401
I'll get those teas.

01:32:23.337 --> 01:32:24.871
Sweet.

01:32:24.873 --> 01:32:27.941
You're just loving this,
aren't you?

01:32:27.943 --> 01:32:31.244
The attention, the spotlight,
the fame?

01:32:31.246 --> 01:32:33.079
You haven't changed one bit.

01:32:33.081 --> 01:32:36.049
What are you suggesting?
That is disgusting.

01:32:36.051 --> 01:32:37.951
Hey, drop the act,
Leanne, please.

01:32:37.953 --> 01:32:39.152
I know the truth.

01:32:39.154 --> 01:32:40.854
Yes, of course, you do.
Everybody does.

01:32:40.856 --> 01:32:41.855
They saw it
on the press conference

01:32:41.857 --> 01:32:43.256
on television today.

01:32:43.258 --> 01:32:45.191
Yeah, I saw it as well,
and I'd have to say

01:32:45.193 --> 01:32:48.028
if I didn't know you were
lying through your teeth,

01:32:48.030 --> 01:32:49.262
I'd have believed every word.

01:32:49.264 --> 01:32:52.265
What? Are you trying
to slander me?

01:32:52.267 --> 01:32:55.101
Slander?

01:32:55.103 --> 01:32:56.870
No, no, no, no.

01:32:56.872 --> 01:32:58.371
The word is expose.

01:32:59.407 --> 01:33:01.241
Ok, what is this?

01:33:01.243 --> 01:33:04.110
You still have a little bug
up your ass about high school?

01:33:04.112 --> 01:33:06.146
Oh, no, this is
so much more than that.

01:33:06.148 --> 01:33:09.716
I followed you to that cabin
in the middle of nowhere.

01:33:09.718 --> 01:33:13.053
Imagine my surprise to see
all the key players there.

01:33:13.055 --> 01:33:16.156
You, Billy, JT,

01:33:16.158 --> 01:33:18.925
and your missing child.

01:33:22.163 --> 01:33:25.732
Wow. You look worried.

01:33:25.734 --> 01:33:27.200
Are you Ok?

01:33:29.404 --> 01:33:31.304
You have no idea
how good it feels

01:33:31.306 --> 01:33:32.939
after all these years

01:33:32.941 --> 01:33:35.842
to just knock that snotty
look off your face.

01:33:38.179 --> 01:33:39.913
Oh, and don't get
any crazy ideas either

01:33:39.915 --> 01:33:41.715
because if anything
happens to me,

01:33:41.717 --> 01:33:44.284
I've made arrangements
for the story to be released.

01:33:48.255 --> 01:33:49.255
Oh.

01:33:51.092 --> 01:33:53.193
I'm afraid you're going down,

01:33:53.195 --> 01:33:56.229
and I'm so happy
to be the one to do it.

01:33:59.233 --> 01:34:00.300
Fuck.

01:34:03.070 --> 01:34:04.070
Wait! Shh!

01:34:07.908 --> 01:34:08.908
Please.

01:34:17.084 --> 01:34:18.785
You want money for the iced tea?

01:34:18.787 --> 01:34:20.854
No, just sit down, please.

01:34:20.856 --> 01:34:23.189
I want to explain this time.
The truth, for real.

01:34:24.258 --> 01:34:25.525
I know you'll understand.

01:34:29.430 --> 01:34:32.465
Ok, Billy and I did reconnect.

01:34:34.168 --> 01:34:36.402
Don and I were going through
a really hard time,

01:34:36.404 --> 01:34:38.471
and I just talked to Billy,

01:34:38.473 --> 01:34:41.074
and he made me feel
so good about myself,

01:34:41.076 --> 01:34:42.442
but then when I realized

01:34:42.444 --> 01:34:44.511
I couldn't really
go through with it,

01:34:44.513 --> 01:34:46.813
Billy went ballistic.

01:34:46.815 --> 01:34:49.783
He started threatening me,
and then he kidnapped Patty,

01:34:49.785 --> 01:34:51.951
and told me
that if I didn't leave don,

01:34:51.953 --> 01:34:54.454
he would keep her
or maybe do worse,

01:34:55.956 --> 01:34:58.558
and so I figured
I couldn't hurt don

01:34:58.560 --> 01:35:00.560
any more than I already had,

01:35:00.562 --> 01:35:03.530
and I would just
play along with Billy

01:35:03.532 --> 01:35:06.099
until maybe he would
just let Patty go.

01:35:06.101 --> 01:35:08.168
Somehow I figured
I could convince him.

01:35:08.170 --> 01:35:10.470
I thought you were going to
tell me the truth.

01:35:10.472 --> 01:35:12.038
That doesn't add up,

01:35:12.040 --> 01:35:13.360
and you didn't have to
kill Billy.

01:35:14.341 --> 01:35:15.341
I...

01:35:17.077 --> 01:35:18.578
JT did.

01:35:18.580 --> 01:35:20.213
He had to.

01:35:20.215 --> 01:35:22.015
He was threatening Patty.

01:35:23.117 --> 01:35:25.919
Listen, as far as I'm concerned,

01:35:25.921 --> 01:35:27.887
all signs point
to you being the killer,

01:35:27.889 --> 01:35:31.424
and regardless,
you withheld information

01:35:31.426 --> 01:35:33.393
in an abduction
of your own child.

01:35:33.395 --> 01:35:36.462
Well, he was blackmailing me.
What was I supposed to do?

01:35:36.464 --> 01:35:39.299
He said if I called the cops,
he would kill himself and Patty.

01:35:40.568 --> 01:35:42.202
He was crazy.

01:35:42.204 --> 01:35:44.304
He was not the Billy
we knew from high school.

01:35:45.606 --> 01:35:48.608
I don't know, leanne.

01:35:48.610 --> 01:35:51.044
That's just it. You don't know.

01:35:52.279 --> 01:35:54.280
And how can you ruin
my entire family

01:35:54.282 --> 01:35:57.217
based on something that you're
really not sure about?

01:35:59.286 --> 01:36:01.521
Not to mention,
most people might think that

01:36:01.523 --> 01:36:03.356
you're just trying
to put yourself in the limelight

01:36:03.358 --> 01:36:05.124
by using my tragedy.

01:36:05.126 --> 01:36:08.061
- Oh, that's ridiculous.
- Yeah, I know it is. It is.

01:36:08.063 --> 01:36:09.229
Yeah.

01:36:09.231 --> 01:36:12.098
I know, but you,
you of all people,

01:36:12.100 --> 01:36:14.500
know the media
and how they can spin things.

01:36:14.502 --> 01:36:16.970
And a lot of people
are going to wonder

01:36:16.972 --> 01:36:19.372
why you didn't go
to the police first.

01:36:19.374 --> 01:36:21.641
I was about to break the news.

01:36:21.643 --> 01:36:23.076
I just had to finish
my investigation

01:36:23.078 --> 01:36:24.444
and gather my evidence

01:36:24.446 --> 01:36:27.180
before I presented it
to the authorities.

01:36:27.182 --> 01:36:30.583
I think it's far from
a slam dunk for you.

01:36:30.585 --> 01:36:34.220
I think you might become
the laughing stock of the media.

01:36:40.060 --> 01:36:41.227
I have an idea.

01:36:43.932 --> 01:36:47.934
I have an idea that might put
both of us on top.

01:37:06.387 --> 01:37:08.187
Oh, you know what,

01:37:08.189 --> 01:37:10.990
will you take a look at this
for me?

01:37:10.992 --> 01:37:13.192
Thank you.
Did I mess up my face?

01:37:17.498 --> 01:37:19.666
I think you look great.
Think we look great.

01:37:19.668 --> 01:37:22.468
I think we're ready. Thank you.

01:37:22.470 --> 01:37:25.571
All right, we're on in five,

01:37:25.573 --> 01:37:28.074
- and cue music.
- Four, three...

01:37:30.411 --> 01:37:33.246
Good evening, I'm Nancy Nelson.

01:37:33.248 --> 01:37:37.250
Tonight, I'm joined
by a mother and survivor,

01:37:37.252 --> 01:37:39.585
Mrs. Leanne Wilson.

01:37:39.587 --> 01:37:42.221
She is giving us
the first interview

01:37:42.223 --> 01:37:44.490
since she was reunited
with her daughter, Patty,

01:37:44.492 --> 01:37:46.459
who was missing...

01:37:46.461 --> 01:37:50.063
Please welcome,
your host, Ms. Leanne Wilson!

01:37:54.601 --> 01:37:55.601
Oh, wow. Thank you.

01:37:59.073 --> 01:38:02.375
Oh, thank you,
thank you so much.

01:38:02.377 --> 01:38:06.612
Oh, I just wanted to say...
Oh, thank you so much.

01:38:06.614 --> 01:38:08.414
Wow, wow.

01:38:08.416 --> 01:38:11.351
This is really
such an amazing thing

01:38:11.353 --> 01:38:14.120
to happen to our family,

01:38:14.122 --> 01:38:15.488
after so much tragedy,

01:38:15.490 --> 01:38:18.291
to have such a victory
and to be here with you.

01:38:18.293 --> 01:38:20.059
Oh!

01:38:20.061 --> 01:38:22.362
All my life I wanted to do
something to empower women.

01:38:58.565 --> 01:39:02.168
Ok, we're ready for you.
Are you ready, Patty?

01:39:05.672 --> 01:39:07.073
Are you excited?

01:39:08.442 --> 01:39:10.143
You're not nervous are you?

01:39:11.245 --> 01:39:13.346
Ok, we're gonna go up here.

01:39:13.348 --> 01:39:14.747
We're gonna be
a little bit quiet

01:39:14.749 --> 01:39:18.251
'cause they already
started taping, Ok?

01:39:18.253 --> 01:39:19.419
It's just coming up here.

01:39:21.188 --> 01:39:24.424
Oh, and look,
that's your mom on TV.

01:39:25.793 --> 01:39:26.793
Let's go.

01:39:28.629 --> 01:39:30.596
Come on, y'all.

01:39:30.598 --> 01:39:35.334
Let's give a round of applause
all round. Thank you so much.

01:39:44.078 --> 01:39:45.778
I am Leanne Wilson,

01:39:45.780 --> 01:39:48.815
and this is our
very first Leanne show.

01:39:48.817 --> 01:39:50.283
Thank you so much for being here

01:39:50.285 --> 01:39:52.819
and saying so many
wonderful things,

01:39:52.821 --> 01:39:54.654
giving me the hope and faith

01:39:54.656 --> 01:39:57.356
that I have today
to share with you...

01:40:00.694 --> 01:40:01.861
Little Ms. Patty Wilson.

01:40:03.697 --> 01:40:05.665
She's backstage
with her father right now,

01:40:05.667 --> 01:40:07.400
but she'll be out here
any second.

01:40:09.837 --> 01:40:11.270
Thank you so much
for being here.

01:40:11.272 --> 01:40:12.839
In a minute,
you are going to meet

01:40:12.841 --> 01:40:15.308
the most beautiful and talented
little girl in the world,

01:40:17.211 --> 01:40:19.145
my daughter, Patty Wilson.

01:40:52.547 --> 01:40:54.881
My mother kidnapped me.

